  "market_context": "Daily price action around July 19, 2023, where both ES and NQ formed a swing high on the same date (Wednesday, July 19), but diverged afterward—ES extended higher while NQ reversed sharply downward, setting up a Smart Money Technique (SMT) divergence.",
  "key_observation": "On July 19, ES and NQ both formed a swing high, but ES subsequently made a higher high while NQ failed to retest that level and instead formed a lower high, indicating relative weakness in NQ and relative strength in ES.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the shared swing high on Wednesday, July 19, 2023, on both ES1! and NQ1! daily charts.",
    "Step 2: Observe that after the July 19 swing high, ES formed a higher high on the next candle while NQ produced a large bearish candle and did not retest the prior high.",
    "Step 3: Note that ES later broke above the July 19 swing high, whereas NQ failed to even approach it, confirming the divergence.",
    "Step 4: Classify this as an SMT (Smart Money Technique) divergence: ES higher high vs. NQ lower high, signaling relative strength in ES and relative weakness in NQ.",
    "Step 5: Use this divergence to infer trade bias: prefer short setups in NQ and long setups in ES."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When two correlated assets form a swing point on the same date, divergence in subsequent swing structure (higher vs. lower high/low) is a high-probability SMT signal for relative strength/weakness—critical for selecting the optimal asset for entries.",
